I finally found a solution... In iOS &lt;= 12, leaving exchange parameters empty when trying to use ecdhKeyExchangeStandardX963SHA256 algorithm was falling back to using SecKeyAlgorithm.ecdhKeyExchangeCofactor.

Therefore the fix to reproduce previous behavior is to modify the SecKeyCopyKeyExchangeResult with 

    
    // generate shared secret
    let exchangeOptions: [String: Any] = [:]
    guard let shared = SecKeyCopyKeyExchangeResult(secKey, SecKeyAlgorithm.ecdhKeyExchangeCofactor, otherKey, exchangeOptions as CFDictionary, &amp;error) else {
      XCTAssertTrue(false)
      return
    }

This works at least for iOS 10 to 13

